1. The pythonic way to do it is from the [PEP 8 style guide](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/):
For sequences, (strings, lists, tuples), use the fact that empty sequences are false:
```python
# Correct:
if not seq:
if seq:
# Wrong:
if len(seq):
if not len(seq):
```

2. Use `[ ]` instead of `list()` (and its faster to initialize)

